    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
        <body>
            <div rend="parallel">
                <p xml:id="KT382-kilavi">paruvavaraviṉkaṇ vēṟupaṭṭa talaimakaḷait tōḻi “paruvam aṉṟu vampu”
                    eṉṟu vaṟpuṟīiyatu. </p>


                <p xml:lang="en">The confidante, saying “it is not the season,
                    [it is] out of time”, encouraging HER, who had changed at the coming of the
                    season. </p>
            </div>

            <div rend="parallel">
                <lg xml:id="KT382">
                    <l> taṇṭuḷik kēṟṟa paiṅkoṭi mullai</l>
                    <l> mukaitalai tiṟanta nāṟṟam putaṉmicaip</l>
                    <l> pūmali taḷavamoṭu tēṅkamaḻpu kañala</l>
                    <l> vampum peyyumār maḻaiyē vampaṉṟu</l>
                    <l> kāritu paruva māyiṉ</l>
                    <l> vārā rōnaṅ kāta lōrē.</l>


                </lg>

                <lg xml:lang="en">
                    <l> Out of time <note place="foot">
                            <term xml:lang="ta">vampu</term> (DEDR 5252 "instability") is attested
                        only here in the KT (as well as once in AN, thrice in NA, and occasionally
                        in the <term xml:lang="ta">kiḷavi-s</term> ). Cām. glosses "raining at a
                        time out of time" ( <term xml:lang="ta">kālam allāta kālattu peyyum</term>
                        ), and this certainly makes sense, even if it stretches semantics.</note>
                        too indeed rains the rain,</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> so that the jasmine in fresh creepers, exposed to the cool
                        drops,</l>
                    <l rend="indent"> is dense, smelling of honey, together with the red jasmine</l>
                    <l rend="indent8"> full of flowers,</l>
                    <l rend="indent2"> on the fragrant shrubs, where the bud heads have opened.</l>
                    <l> If it is not out of time [and] this [is] the rainy season</l>
                    <l> won't he come, our lover?</l>


                </lg>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
